# {{GAME_NAME}}

Scaffolded by `zenith new {{GAME_NAME}}`. A minimal Zenith game: one lit cube
that bobs up and down. Replace the component logic with your own game.

## File structure

```
Games/{{GAME_NAME}}/
  {{GAME_NAME}}.zproj                       # Build descriptor (name, android flag, extras)
  {{GAME_NAME}}.cpp                         # Project_* entry points + component registration
  Components/{{GAME_NAME}}_GameComponent.h  # The starter component (spawns + bobs a cube)
  Tests/{{GAME_NAME}}_BootCharacterization.cpp  # Boot test (game component resolves)
  Assets/Scenes/                            # Main.zscen is BOOT-AUTHORED (see below)
  CLAUDE.md                                 # This file
```

## Build & run

New games are managed by the `zenith` CLI (no Sharpmake edits):

```
zenith build {{GAME_NAME}}          # Vulkan_vs2022_Debug_Win64_True
zenith run   {{GAME_NAME}}          # launch the newest built exe
zenith open  {{GAME_NAME}}          # regen + open the solution in Visual Studio
```

Or directly:

```
msbuild Games\{{GAME_NAME}}\{{GAME_NAME_LOWER}}_win64.sln /t:{{GAME_NAME}} /p:Configuration=Vulkan_vs2022_Debug_Win64_True /p:Platform=x64
Games\{{GAME_NAME}}\Build\output\win64\vulkan_vs2022_debug_win64_true\{{GAME_NAME_LOWER}}.exe
```

## First-run scene caveat (IMPORTANT)

`Assets/Scenes/Main.zscen` is **not checked in** -- it is authored on boot by
`Project_RegisterEditorAutomationSteps` (a **tools-only** function) and saved via
`AddStep_SaveScene`. Because that function is compiled out of non-tools builds:

* Your **first build + run must be a `*_True` config** (e.g.
  `Vulkan_vs2022_Debug_Win64_True`). That boot authors and saves `Main.zscen`.
* Thereafter, `*_False` and Android builds **load** the baked `Main.zscen`.

If a `_False` build shows an empty scene, run a `_True` build once to bake it.

## Where to go next

* `Components/{{GAME_NAME}}_GameComponent.h` -- lifecycle hooks (`OnStart`,
  `OnUpdate`, `WriteToDataStream`/`ReadFromDataStream`) are concept-detected by
  the component-meta registry; there is no base class.
* `{{GAME_NAME}}.cpp` -- the `Project_*` contract + the boot-authored scene.
* For richer examples: `Games/Combat` (multi-scene + Behaviour Graphs),
  `Games/DevilsPlayground` (physics), `Games/RenderTest` (rendering showcase).

## Android

This game is win64-only (`"android": false` in `{{GAME_NAME}}.zproj`). To add an
Android build: copy an existing game's `Android/` Gradle tree (e.g.
`Games/Combat/Android`), retarget its package/name, set `"android": true` in the
descriptor, and run `zenith regen`.
